        <section id="nouns-animals">
            <h>animals</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=cat">cat</a> beag</g>
                <en>a little cat</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha an cat beag.</gd>
                        <tr>The cat is small.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha an cat beag bàn aig an teine.</gd>
                        <tr>The little white cat is by the fire.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 9</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha cù mór dubh aig Calum ach tha cat beag bòidheach aig Màiri.</gd>
                        <tr>Malcolm has a big black dog but Mary has a pretty little cat.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 25</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=uan">uan</a> beag</g>
                <en>a little lamb</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Bha an crodh blàth le teas na gréine agus bha iad ’nan seasamh anns na
                            lochan beaga a bha an siud ’s an seo air feadh a’ mhonaidh. Bha na
                            h-uain bheaga a’ leum agus a’ cluich mu thimcheall am màthraichean.</gd>
                        <tr>The cattle were warm with the heat of the sun and they were standing in
                            the little lakes which were here and there throughout the moor. The
                            little lambs were jumping and playing about their mothers.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 146</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=eun">eun</a> beag</g>
                <en>a little bird</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Chunnaic mi eun beag ann an craoibh agus iolair air creig.</gd>
                        <tr>I saw a little bird in a tree and an eagle on a rock.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 236</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="nouns-artifacts">
            <h>artifacts</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=baata">bàta</a> beag</g>
                <en>a small boat</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Bha bàta beag air an traigh.</gd>
                        <tr>There was a little boat on the beach.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 21 [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl></p>
        </section>
        <section id="nouns-geography">
            <h>geography</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=loch">loch</a> beag</g>
                <en>a small lake</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Bha Calum sgìth a’ coiseachd air a’ mhonadh, ach mu dheireadh ràinig e
                            mullach na beinne. [...] Bha latha briagha ann agus bha a’ ghrian a’
                            deàrrsadh. [...] Bha an crodh blàth le teas na gréine agus bha iad ’nan
                            seasamh anns na lochan beaga a bha an siud ’s an seo air feadh a’
                            mhonaidh.</gd>
                        <tr>Malcolm was tired walking on the moor, but at last he reached the top of
                            the mountain. [...] It was a beautiful day and the sun was shining.
                            [...] The cattle were warm with the heat of the sun and they were
                            standing in the little lakes which were here and there throughout the
                            moor.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 146</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section id="adjs">
        <h>adjectives</h>
        <p><g><a href="?gd=moor">mór</a> agus beag</g>
            <en>big and small</en> – <xl>
                <li>
                    <gd>Tha an cù mór ach tha an cat beag.</gd>
                    <tr>The dog is big but the cat is small.</tr>
                    <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <gd>Tha Màiri beag ach tha Calum mór.</gd>
                    <tr>Mary is small but Malcolm is big.</tr>
                    <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
                </li>
            </xl>
        </p>
    </section>

